;B[cd]
;W[cc]C[If he should push through at D15, D14, C15, Black will squeeze with D17, C17, E17, C16, then connect at B14.  White has to answer with the tiger's mouth at B18, whereupon Black either connects at E13 or joins up at B12. In addition to the ko potential left in the corner White will have many defects and he will find it difficult to cope.]
;B[ce]
;W[bc]
;B[bh]C[He can take the corner with D18, but then White simply captures C10. While the trade is roughly equal, White still has chances of living in the corner.]
